reviewText: Anita Ekberg plays the much-abused wife of the Sterling Hayden character in this movie which looks mighty like a western. She's finally rescued by her real-life husband of 3 years in the '50s, Anthony Steel -- but only after Hayden scars and shoots her, and lfinally leaves her in the hands of a jury that seens bent on hanging her, not him.
Very hard-to-get film. I enjoyed this and earlier bought film poster of "Valerie"
Not really a western, but a court case. Unusual premise for a western. Unusual casting in two of the lead roles , Englands' Anthony Steele and European sex bomb Anita Ekberg.
